From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 02:15:47 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] freedreno/drm: add a KGSL winsys backend for downstream
 a5xx

The Moto G7 Play (channel; SDM632/msm8953, Adreno 506 = a5xx) runs a downstream
4.9 kernel whose only GPU driver is Qualcomm's KGSL.  There is no drm/msm driver
and no DRM render node at all: the GPU is reached through the character device
/dev/kgsl-3d0 and a set of KGSL ioctls.  freedreno's winsys only ships msm and
virtio backends, so on such a device the gallium driver has nothing to bind to.

Add a kgsl backend implementing the fd_device / fd_pipe / fd_bo / ringbuffer
funcs against the KGSL uAPI:

  kgsl_device.c         device open and funcs dispatch
  kgsl_pipe.c           context create, submit, timestamp wait, ->retired
  kgsl_bo.c             GPU object alloc / import / map / deferred free
  kgsl_ringbuffer_sp.c  cmdstream submit on the _sp ringbuffer
  kgsl_priv.h           shared backend definitions
  README.aosp.md        provenance and the delta over the community base

The code descends from the freedreno community KGSL winsys (Mesa MR !21570 and
the termux/xMeM lineage), with portions borrowed from turnip's KGSL support
(tu_kgsl.c); both are MIT and the per-file headers record this.  It is not a
rebase onto a maintained fork: no maintained GL-gallium KGSL fork exists (xMeM
carries only the Vulkan/turnip backend, and turnip has no a5xx support at all),
so the backend is carried downstream.

Relative to that community base this fixes a systemic premature-BO-free, seen as
kernel "GPU PAGE FAULT (write translation fault)" plus silent corruption: the
deferred-free fallback for buffers the submit path never added to fs->bos read a
lazily-updated, unsynchronised device-global last-submit timestamp that a free
could outrun via the async submit queue.  The last-submit record is now packed
into a single 64-bit word and published/read atomically so the (ctx, ts) pair is
always consistent, and the deferred GPUOBJ_FREE_ON_EVENT fallback now covers any
externally-shared buffer (KGSL_BO_IMPORT, FD_BO_SHARED or FD_BO_SCANOUT), not
just imports.  kgsl_pipe_retired() implements the fd_pipe_funcs.retired hook by
reading KGSL_TIMESTAMP_RETIRED, which closes the matching bo-cache recycle race.

fd_device_new()'s dispatch already had a vestigial kgsl arm behind
#if HAVE_FREEDRENO_KGSL, but nothing ever defined that macro and the arm keyed
off drmGetVersion()->name -- which cannot work here, since /dev/kgsl-3d0 is not
a DRM node and drmGetVersion() simply fails on the fd.  Treat a failing
drmGetVersion() as "assume kgsl" instead of fatal, and guard the remaining
version->name comparisons so they are never reached with a NULL version.

The backend is opt-in through the existing -Dfreedreno-kmds= option, which
already lists kgsl as a valid choice; selecting it now compiles the backend in
and defines HAVE_FREEDRENO_KGSL.
